<paragraph blockId="15.[805,1401,272,700]" pageId="15" pageNumber="264">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[1136,1303,272,305]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Heterogeomys</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Heterogeomys</taxonomicName>
was considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Orthogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Orthogeomys</taxonomicName>
by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that H. hispidusis sister to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Elliot" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[806,931,509,542]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lanius">H. lanius</taxonomicName>
. Twelve subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
